pageContext.claim: “And if you read, Tim Cook of Apple said that they are now in full operation again in China...You probably saw that -- as I mentioned, Tim just came out and he said Apple is back to normal in terms of production in their facilities in China. They've made a lot of progress.”
pageContext.analysis: Cook, the chief executive of Apple, was not as rosy about the Chinese operations as Trump claimed: "When you look at the parts that are done in China, we have reopened factories, so the factories were able to work through the conditions to reopen. They're reopening. They're also in ramp, and so I think of this as sort of the third phase of getting back to normal. And we're in phase three of the ramp mode."
